Kaveel Singh, News24Maite Nkoana-Mashabane Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; International Relations Minister Maite Nkoana-Mashabane on Sunday declared her weekend visit to China a &ldquo;success&rdquo;.Nkoana-Mashabane met with her counterpart, Foreign Minister Wang Yi and paid a courtesy call on Vice Minister of Finance SHI Yaobin.China is currently involved in several important development projects in SA, the department of international relations and co-operation said. The department said Nkoana-Mashabane &ldquo;discussed issues of mutual interest&rdquo; with her Chinese counterparts.The department said the Nkoana-Mashabane discussed the status of BRICS projects and took stock of progress made as the co-chairs of the Forum on China-Africa Co-operation (FOCAC). China, the current chair of BRICS, will host the 9th BRICS Leaders&rsquo; Summit in Xiamen, Fujian Province, from 3-5 September. SA will host the summit in 2018.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.